[center]
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=6][b]Simple Location Manager[/b][/size][/color]
<br />[i]Save, Organise, and Share your favourite spots in Night City.[/i][/center]
<br />[line]
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Overview[/b][/size][/color]
<br />Ever found a preem photo spot, a hidden gem, or a great testing location, only to lose it forever? [b]Simple Location Manager[/b] is a UI tool for Cyber Engine Tweaks that lets you save, organise, and share locations with ease.
<br />
<br />[b]Simple Location Manager[/b] is designed for organisation first. It automatically detects your location, identifying the District and sub-district, and organises your locations into a clean, collapsible hierarchy.
<br />
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=4][b]New in v1.1.0[/b][/size][/color]
<br />[list]
<br />[*][b]Custom Categories:[/b] create, edit, and share your own categories with unique custom icons.
<br />[*][b]AMM Support:[/b] import Appearance Menu Mod locations. 
<br />[*][b]Presets:[/b] support for installing location packs with auto-installing categories.
<br />[/list]
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Key Features[/b][/size][/color]
<br />[list]
<br />[*][b]Save Anywhere:[/b] Instantly record your position. Add custom names, descriptions, or let the mod auto-timestamp them.
<br />[*][b]Smart Organisation:[/b] Locations are automatically grouped by [b]District[/b] or [b]Category[/b].
<br />[*][b]Favorites:[/b] Keep your most-used spots at the top of the list for instant access.
<br />[*][b]Custom Categories (New):[/b] Create your own categories (e.g., "Stunts", "Photos") and assign them unique icons.
<br />[*][b]AMM Support (New):[/b] Import existing locations created for Appearance Menu Mod. [i]AMM is [b]not[/b] required for this to work.[/i] 
<br />[*][b]Powerful Search:[/b] Filter by name, district, or description in real-time.
<br />[*][b]Import / Export:[/b] Share locations with your choombas! Copy a single spot, a whole district, or your entire database to the clipboard as a text string.
<br />[*][b]Navigation:[/b] One-click to set a [b]Custom Map Pin[/b] to any saved location. [i]Works great with Autodrive![/i]
<br />[*][b]Lazy Mode (Teleport):[/b] Optional feature to instantly teleport to any saved spot (Disabled by default).
<br />[*][b]Customizable:[/b][list]
<br />[*]Adjust duplicate warning distance.
<br />[*]Choose if groups start Expanded or Collapsed.
<br />[*]Toggle extra UI details like raw coordinates.
<br />[*]Group locations by [b]District [/b]or [b]Category[/b].
<br />[/list]
<br />[/list][line]
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Installation[/b][/size][/color]
<br />[b]Requirements:[/b]
<br />[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/107]Cyber Engine Tweaks[/url] (Latest Version)
<br />
<br />[b]How to Install:[/b]
<br />[list=1]
<br />[*] Download the mod.
<br />[*] Extract the [font=Courier New]bin[/font] folder to your Cyberpunk 2077 root directory.
<br />[i]*Final Path should look like:* [font=Courier New]Cyberpunk 2077&#92;bin&#92;x64&#92;plugins&#92;cyber_engine_tweaks&#92;mods&#92;SimpleLocationManager&#92;[/font][/i]
<br />[/list]
<br />[line]
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Usage[/b][/size][/color]
<br />[list=1]
<br />[*] Open the CET Overlay (chosen during CET install).
<br />[*] The [b]Simple Location Manager[/b] window will appear.
<br />[*] Click [b]"+"[/b] to save your current spot.
<br />[/list]
<br />[line]
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]For Mod Authors: Create Presets[/b][/size][/color]
<br />Want to publish a list of locations? (Hidden gems, photo spots, stash houses?)
<br />[b]Simple Location Manager[/b] supports [b]Presets[/b] that allow you to distribute locations easily.
<br />
<br />[list]
<br />[*]Create a [font=Courier New].txt[/font] file with your exported locations.
<br />[*]Users simply install your mod with the preset file in the [font=Courier New]presets[/font] folder, and it will automatically show in the locations list.
<br />[*][b]Custom Categories Auto-Install:[/b] If you use a custom category (e.g., "My Stash" with a specific icon), it will [b]automatically be created[/b] for the user when they load your preset. No manual setup required!
<br />[/list]
<br />[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/articles/1960][b]Read the full guide on creating Presets here[/b][/url]
<br />[line]
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=5][b]Import / Export[/b][/size][/color]
<br />To export a location, click on the export button on the location. A simple code string will be added to your clipboard. This can be pasted for easy sharing/backup.
<br />Importing a location is as simple as pasting that export string into the import window found under the settings tab.
<br />
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=4][b]Import from AMM[/b][/size][/color]
<br />You can now import existing Appearance Menu Mod locations!
<br />[b][i]AMM is not required to be installed for this to work.
<br />[/i][/b]
<br />[list]
<br />[*][b]Bulk Import (For Appearance Menu Mod):[/b]
<br />[list=1]
<br />[*]Install the AMM location mod as per the mod's instructions. [i](Remember to endorse it!)[/i]
<br />[*]Copy the .json files from the AMM folder:
<br />[font=Courier New]bin&#92;x64&#92;plugins&#92;cyber_engine_tweaks&#92;mods&#92;AppearanceMenuMod&#92;User&#92;Locations[/font]
<br />to the SLM import folder:
<br />[font=Courier New]bin&#92;x64&#92;plugins&#92;cyber_engine_tweaks&#92;mods&#92;SimpleLocationManager&#92;import[/font]
<br />[*]Load the game, open SLM &gt; Settings Tab &gt; Import Button &gt; "AMM Bulk Import" tab.
<br />[*]Click "Scan Directory &amp; Import".
<br />[/list][/list]
<br />[list][*][b]Manual Import:[/b] Simply paste the content from any AMM JSON file into the import box, and it will be automatically detected and converted.
<br />[/list]
<br />[color=#ffff00][size=4][b]SLM Export Strings[/b][/size][/color]
<br />These strings can be shared with other users of the mod, or as a way to back up your list of locations (Export all button in the settings tab).
<br />
